CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 11, 1956, pg. 7 reads: "Check to Polio Fund - Hill City, Radio Station WILY and Ammon Recreation Center contributed $239.30, raised at a recent basketball game and dance to the polio fund last week. Miss Pricilla Ward, member of the Hill City welfare department (second from right), is shown as she presents Hill City's check for its part of the proceeds from the affair to Mrs. Eunice Cook, Hill District chairman of the polio fund.  Ammon Center contributed its half through the City Bureau of Recreation.  Bill Powell of Radio Station WILY is at the extreme left. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bill Powell, Eunice Cook receiving check for Polio Fund from Pricilla Ward, and unknown man, standing in interior
